6. gamma (Euler-Mascheroni) — HARD CASE
----------------------------------------
   Status: Convergence boundary.
   Direct harmonic series: error ~ 1/(2n)
   For 100 digits need n ~ 10^100 terms — infeasible
   with naive method in rational arithmetic.

   This is the honest boundary of the naive approach.
   Specialized acceleration (Brent-McMillan) exists
   but requires careful rational implementation.
   Flagged as open challenge in the paper.

================================================================================
SUMMARY: Canonical Rational Basis for Physical Constants
================================================================================

  Constant   Method                    Terms/Iter   100-digit match
  ---------- ------------------------- ------------ ---------------
  pi         Machin formula            75 terms     YES
  e          Taylor 1/n!               80 terms     YES
  ln(2)      2*arctanh(1/3)            120 terms    YES
  sqrt(2)    Newton method             10 iter      YES
  phi        Newton method             10 iter      YES
  gamma      (open challenge)          —            BOUNDARY

  All pairs are (numerator, denominator) where both are pure integers.
  All arithmetic is exact rational — no floats at any stage.
  At 100 decimal digits, rational and transcendental are identical.
  Planck length is ~10^-35 meters. These exceed that by 65 orders.
  No physical process can distinguish the rational from the transcendental.
  